chalkie/chalky
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a Stock Exchange employee who records the sale of each share traded on the chalk board of the Stock Exchange.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: transf. from Stock Exchange chalkie to restaurant chalkie [Also used as pseudonym for financial columnist]
